Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on speaker verification using audio data, which falls under the sound category.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper proposes a new alignment mechanism to extract supervectors, which involves natural language processing techniques such as text alignment.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel back-end approach to train a neural network for detection tasks, which falls under the machine learning category.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not explicitly mention computer vision, the proposed alignment mechanism and back-end approach can be seen as a form of feature extraction and classification, which are common tasks in computer vision.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes new techniques to improve the performance of speaker verification systems, which can be seen as a form of artificial intelligence research.
